review_text:
What more can you ask for, i have learnt a lot in this course, i only wish some of your example photos looks into product photography as well, i feel loaded, now i can handle my camera with more confidence.

Thanks.

Basically good. I missed some things, or many things were only superficially mentioned. This is also clear, considering the length of the course, but I would have expected more information on various topics, instead there is a lot of "filling material". I am curious if what I learned will help to make better photos.
Great job! Awesome teaching skills.
Great course with a lot of great information.
Very useful course for beginners! I'm not a beginner but i wanted to try it anyway just a revision and it's really good. Now i will wait for a "Photography Mastery" Course Sean!

Starting with a challenge is an awesome way to capture your attention as you start the course. For people like me who are starting to incur in photography as a hobby, I think this course will help a lot. Granted, I would like to have Sean there evaluating the images I take but his recommendation to reach out to other photographers should help me get on my way. 
Sean, this was a great course and I am looking forward to taking your next courses.
This course was really insightful and I hope that the information I learnt in it can be used practically.

I really enjoyed taking this course. I didn't have any experience with photography but now I feel I understand the basics and I am a lot more confident when taking photos. The information in this course is presented in a simple and clear way suitable for a beginner. I didn't feel overwhelmed by the unfamiliar concepts, on the contrary, this course made me feel excited to go out there and practice what I've learned. Thank you so much for a great experience :)
this was short to the point and easy to understand.
I really like how easy it is to understand. I like the quizzes in between to help recapture the knowledge.
Great course with relevant content. I will be going back to it as much as I need to.

Sean really knows his stuff. He helped me to understand things that I've spent lots of time trying to learn from others. though I only own a bridge camera at this time, I hope to invest in a DSLR or mirrorless camera to practice and eventually become a professional.

Lots of gems and helpful information! It's definitely a basic course and not everything was relevant for me, but it was a lot more straight forward and clearly explained than a lot of confusing online guides that I've read. Great personality, energy, and examples, too!
Loved it!
It is a very good basic Photography course. I fully recommend it. Thank you very much.
Good course would recommend
Amazing course! Thanks for your Tips!

Sean's course is amazing, I am a photographer who has taken a year out of shooting and wanted to to a short course as a refresher, I couldn't have picked a better tutor. Sean is so informative, laying his knowledge out perfectly and so easy to digest. I cannot recommend him highly enough!
Great
The course was very interesting, informative and focused. I enjoyed it very much and feel that received very solid and practical basic methodology to shooting food.
Woow the best so far, great jobüëç
Sean is awesome, the most clear photography course I ever had, fun to watch and and super engaging, thank you!!
Very helpful to understand enough to get started and inspire creativity.
Excellent course
I liked the course. An excellent teacher, everything was accessible and understandable.
Very useful and well explained

Resourceful, simple, fantastic course. As a passionate sport & animal photographer, this course was everything and more to change my relationship with my camera and especially the way I'll use light in the future.
Can't wait for the upcoming courses from you!
